{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"8e5c36b3-1786-46c7-a4d4-29eaca40f73b","content":"Here's the correct attribute for each framework:\n\n| Framework | Attribute |\n|-----------|-----------|\n| **MSTest** | `[Ignore(\"reason\")]` |\n| **xUnit** | `[Fact(Skip = \"reason\")]` or `[Theory(Skip = \"reason\")]` |\n| **NUnit** | `[Ignore(\"reason\")]` |\n| **TUnit** | `[Skip(\"reason\")]` |\n\n**Examples:**\n\n```csharp\n// MSTest\n[TestMethod]\n[Ignore(\"Blocked by bug #1234\")]\npublic void MyMSTest() { }\n\n// xUnit\n[Fact(Skip = \"Blocked by bug #1234\")]\npublic void MyXUnitTest() { }\n\n// NUnit\n[Test]\n[Ignore(\"Blocked by bug #1234\")]\npublic void MyNUnitTest() { }\n\n// TUnit\n[Test]\n[Skip(\"Blocked by bug #1234\")]\npublic async Task MyTUnitTest() { }\n```\n\nAll four frameworks will report these as **skipped** (not failed) in test results, and the reason string appears in the test output.","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"02dc8871-e64b-47af-8d84-9c9171e3365e","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The user is asking about skip/ignore attributes across MSTest, xUnit, NUnit, and TUnit. This is a knowledge question about .NET test frameworks. Let me check if there's a relevant skill - the `dotnet-test-frameworks` skill seems perfect as it contains \"skip annotations\" information.","outputTokens":351,"requestId":"5C22:28F9DD:1C29C3:22B93C:69F54EFE"},"id":"61028e26-71a1-4a38-ae8f-23c3595133e7","timestamp":"2026-05-02T01:10:30.149Z","parentId":"24e83412-4af9-4203-884f-c94530fc7050"}
